# Identity Lifecycle Management — Implementation Tutorial (Northbridge Lab)

## Overview

This tutorial documents how to implement a complete identity lifecycle model in Active Directory using a structured approach.

Instead of managing users manually, the process follows three key lifecycle stages:

- Joiner (Onboarding)
- Mover (Role Change)
- Leaver (Offboarding)

The focus is to maintain consistency between:

- Identity attributes  
- Group-based access  
- Organizational Unit (OU) placement  

This ensures a secure, auditable, and scalable environment.

---

## Environment

- Domain: northbridge.local  
- Platform: Windows Server 2022  
- Service: Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)  
- Tools: PowerShell + RSAT  

### Key OUs

- OU=1.NB_Users
- OU=HR,OU=1.NB_Users
- OU=Finance,OU=1.NB_Users
- OU=IT,OU=1.NB_Users
- OU=Sales,OU=1.NB_Users
- OU=DisabledUsers,OU=1.NB_Users
- OU=5.NB_Groups

---

## 1. Validate Environment

Confirm that the domain and OU structure are correctly configured.

```powershell
Import-Module ActiveDirectory

Get-ADDomain

Get-ADOrganizationalUnit -Filter * | Select Name, DistinguishedName

This ensures the environment is ready before performing lifecycle operations.

2. Review Existing Users

Inspect current users to understand baseline identity attributes.

Get-ADUser -Filter * `
-SearchBase "OU=HR,OU=1.NB_Users,DC=northbridge,DC=local" `
-Properties Department,Title,Manager |
Select Name,Department,Title,Manager

This step helps identify inconsistencies before making changes.

3. Create DisabledUsers OU

Create a dedicated OU for inactive accounts.

New-ADOrganizationalUnit `
-Name "DisabledUsers" `
-Path "OU=1.NB_Users,DC=northbridge,DC=local"

This keeps offboarded accounts isolated and easier to manage.

4. Review RBAC Groups

Verify that access is managed through groups.

Get-ADGroup -Filter * `
-SearchBase "OU=5.NB_Groups,DC=northbridge,DC=local" |
Select Name

This confirms the RBAC structure is ready.

JOINER — ONBOARDING
5. Create New User
New-ADUser `
-Name "Test HR Joiner 01" `
-SamAccountName "test.hrjoiner01" `
-UserPrincipalName "test.hrjoiner01@northbridge.local" `
-Path "OU=HR,OU=1.NB_Users,DC=northbridge,DC=local" `
-AccountPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "TempP@ssw0rd123!" -AsPlainText -Force) `
-Enabled $true

Creates a new user in the HR department.

6. Assign Attributes
Set-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 -Department "HR"
Set-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 -Title "HR Assistant"

Set-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 `
-Manager "CN=Maria Lopez,OU=HR,OU=1.NB_Users,DC=northbridge,DC=local"

Defines identity metadata used for access decisions.

7. Assign Group Membership
Add-ADGroupMember "GRP_HR" -Members "test.hrjoiner01"
Add-ADGroupMember "GRP_StandardUsers" -Members "test.hrjoiner01"

Grants access through RBAC groups.

8. Validate User
Get-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 `
-Properties Enabled,Department,Title |
Select Name,Enabled,Department,Title

Confirms the user is correctly configured.

MOVER — ROLE CHANGE
9. Capture Current State
Get-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 `
-Properties Department,Title |
Select Name,Department,Title

Get-ADPrincipalGroupMembership test.hrjoiner01 |
Select Name

Establishes a baseline before changes.

10. Update Attributes
Set-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 -Department "Finance"
Set-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 -Title "Finance Analyst"

$manager = Get-ADUser dortega
Set-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 -Manager $manager.DistinguishedName

Updates identity to reflect the new role.

11. Update Group Membership
Remove-ADGroupMember "GRP_HR" `
-Members "test.hrjoiner01" `
-Confirm:$false

Add-ADGroupMember "GRP_Finance" `
-Members "test.hrjoiner01"

Removes old access and assigns new permissions.

12. Validate Role Change
Get-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 `
-Properties Department,Title |
Select Name,Department,Title

Get-ADPrincipalGroupMembership test.hrjoiner01 |
Select Name

Ensures attributes and access match the new role.

LEAVER — OFFBOARDING
13. Capture Before State
Get-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 `
-Properties Enabled |
Select Name,Enabled

Confirms the account is active before offboarding.

14. Disable Account
Disable-ADAccount -Identity test.hrjoiner01

Immediately blocks user access.

15. Remove Access
Remove-ADGroupMember "GRP_Finance" `
-Members "test.hrjoiner01" `
-Confirm:$false

Remove-ADGroupMember "GRP_StandardUsers" `
-Members "test.hrjoiner01" `
-Confirm:$false

Ensures no permissions remain.

16. Move to DisabledUsers OU
Move-ADObject `
-Identity (Get-ADUser test.hrjoiner01).DistinguishedName `
-TargetPath "OU=DisabledUsers,OU=1.NB_Users,DC=northbridge,DC=local"

Separates inactive accounts from active users.

17. Validate Offboarding
Get-ADUser test.hrjoiner01 |
Select Name,Enabled,DistinguishedName

Confirms the account is disabled and relocated.

VALIDATION & AUDIT
18. Validate Manager Structure
Get-ADUser mlopez `
-Properties DirectReports |
Select Name,DirectReports

Verifies reporting relationships.

19. Audit User Creation
Get-WinEvent `
-FilterHashtable @{LogName='Security'; Id=4720} `
-MaxEvents 5

Shows user creation events.

20. Audit User Changes
Get-WinEvent `
-FilterHashtable @{LogName='Security'; Id=4738} `
-MaxEvents 5

Shows modifications to user accounts.

21. Audit Disable Event
Get-WinEvent `
-FilterHashtable @{LogName='Security'; Id=4725} `
-MaxEvents 5

Confirms account disable actions.

22. Automation Readiness
Get-ADUser -Filter * `
-SearchBase "OU=1.NB_Users,DC=northbridge,DC=local" `
-Properties Department,Title,Manager |
Select SamAccountName,Department,Title,Manager

Ensures all identities are structured consistently for automation.

Final Result

At the end of this implementation:

Users are onboarded with correct attributes and access
Role changes update identity and permissions consistently
Offboarding removes access and isolates accounts
All actions are traceable through audit logs
The environment is structured for automation and scalability

This reflects how identity lifecycle is handled in real enterprise Active Directory environments.
